snippet.textDisplay:
Sometimes we listen to songs just for fun, without paying attention to the lyrics or the deeper message they carry.
I’ve heard this song by Gurdas Maan ji many times before, but today, I played it with captions on—and it hit differently.

What a powerful and thought-provoking message he conveys!

From the pain of India-Pakistan partition, to the shame we often feel in speaking our own language… from how we blindly adopt others’ cultures while disrespecting our own—this song touches it all. It’s a heartfelt reminder of identity, history, and self-respect.
Everyone should listen to this song at least once with understanding—not just as music, but as a message.
